metadata.name: Paysages Chromatiques A #4
metadata.description:
Taking my inspiration from impressionist and contemporary paintings, I tried to generate 
mixtures of more or less superimposed colors, creating flowing effects or spots as one
would obtain with paint.
This work is the first in a two-part series featuring abstraction and imagination.
I hope it will inspire you to take the time to daydream, or simply to spend a moment 
where the mind can wander freely through the colors.

To save a png file type [s]
TO remove the texture type [t]

To render at higher resolution add &pd=2 at the end of the url in live mode
(others values are valid too but be patient the rendering can be long)
---
100% code made with p5js and glsl

metadata.name: Annum #5289
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of FranÃ§ois Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Olfactory Flow #39
metadata.description:
Olfactory flow field expressions inspired by riso prints and niche perfumes.

/////
Depending on the longevity of the scents, the rendering can take some time.

As soon as the simulation is done (indicated by the subtle texture that appears on top) you can save a 2000x3000px png by pressing 's'.
If you want a high resolution file, please contact me via Twitter (@pxlshrd).

Tip for recent mobile devices: open live view and zoom in while the canvas is drawn.

/////

metadata.name: Momentum #31
metadata.description:
In our new project, we explore the possibilities and tools of generative art. This time we were interested in the aesthetics of particles. When static turns into movement, and the predicted composition becomes spontaneous - the experiment continues.
This project was created with P5.js.
March 2023.
Press 'S' to save a PNG file.

metadata.name: RE/Posizioni #46
metadata.description:
Exactly one year ago I was minting my first fxhash project. 
â€œPosizioniâ€ was a quick sketch of only 25 editions that I put together to test this new platform and to my great surprise, it was the start of an amazing journey in this space that still continues to amaze me every day. 

â€œRE/Posizioniâ€ is an ideal continuation of my personal path that started one year ago: I decided to create an animated, glitchy, or even broken piece, something completely different from what I usually do as an artist and as a coder (and probably something Iâ€™m not very good at, forgive me for this :D ).
Even if this NFT crazy world is often uncertain, insecure, or unstable, we need to find a balance no matter how difficult, just as the lines in this artwork try to do.

Going out of my comfort zone, experimenting, or just having fun is what keeps this creative practice enjoyable for me, and itâ€™s all that matters.

----

- Mouse click to pause the animation
- "s" key to download a png
- "f" key to full screen

Tested on Desktop/Chrome.
